<br>
Average DPS with both setups is about the same (~70 while tanking, ~85 while non-tanking in PoV - thanks to letting a SK hold aggro so I could parse that, with no offensive AAs). Damage taken in PoP from ripostes is nasty with dual wield though. I primarily use my Windblade in PoP unless I have at least two healers (usually my shaman is one of them) or am in a non-PoP zone. <br>
<br>
I don't see why you're getting such different results with a TSBS - unless you have a bunch of offensive 2hander AAs (I don't). <br>
<br>
Umm and I also don't see why you're talking about the slower getting aggro and dying and also holding aggro the whole fight. I two box a shaman, and slow aggro doesn't last that long. One successful taunt is all you need (ok assuming slow wasn't resisted, but it rarely is for me after Malo in PoV/PoS/BoT/PoT) and you've piggybacked over the shaman's aggro. A shaman tanking the whole fight sounds like the warrior wasn't hitting taunt at all, the shaman decided to throw several poison dots on the mob, or the mob was rooted right next to the shaman <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
All in all I absolutely agree with you about Windblade being the best bang for the buck weapon out there though, and normally it probably does outaggro the single red epic.  <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dumeshuhlbelk>Dumesh UhlBelk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 444<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/03 12:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5353.topic&index=22>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://bellsouthpwp.net/w/i/wilsonua/DumStare.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon to pair with Red Blade</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Average DPS with both setups is about the same (~70 while tanking, ~85 while non-tanking in PoV - thanks to letting a SK hold aggro so I could parse that, with no offensive AAs).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Not to sound belligerent, but I would have to see such logs to believe that.  About 6 months ago, I parsed a plain old primal battle axe at 12-15 more dps than a SoD + primal warsword combo in CT.  I tested both setups while tanking, and not tanking.  A windblade should out damage SoD+red epic all day long.  I guess we simply disagree, and since I have reformatted since then, and don't have the logs to post in favor of my viewpoint; my assertion is no more valid than yours.  Even so, I dispute your claim of equivalent dps.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
I don't see why you're getting such different results with a TSBS - unless you have a bunch of offensive 2hander AAs (I don't). <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
As for me, I got my first offensive AA skill last night.  So it was not a factor in my parsed results.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Umm and I also don't see why you're talking about the slower getting aggro and dying and also holding aggro the whole fight. ... One successful taunt is all you need (ok assuming slow wasn't resisted, ...and you've piggybacked over the shaman's aggro. A shaman tanking the whole fight ...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I reread most of the posts here, and I don't see anyone referencing dead shaman or even tanking shaman.  I mentioned shaman that slow mobs before they get to camp (before I can land anything but a few bowshots).  They take aggro for at least a few seconds as I have to move to them and taunt: which as we all know is not a very high success rate, especially if you are 61 and 62 tanking level 60-63 mobs in HoHa.<br>
<br>
There is value in proc'ing one handers.  I use them in the opening seconds of a fight until I land a few procs, or at worst go 30-45 seconds without a proc, which almost never happens.  Then I finish the fight with TSBS.  It does tremendous damage, reduces riposte damage as compared to one handers, and holds taunt just fine as soon as you can pass the hate level of the initial debuffers (or if you get those nice opening rounds of 345, 345, 345, 60 triple + slam). <p><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5309"target="_blank"alt = "Korak's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR = 10,10,900><b>Korak Sarathai - Barbarian Warlord - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12530"target="_blank"alt = "Dumesh's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR = 900,10,10><b>Dumesh Uhl'Belk - Retired Troll Reaver - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a>Those who will not reason are bigots; those who cannot are fools; and those who dare not are slaves. -- Lord Byron
