<br>
I'll see if I can dig up those logs still, but unfortunately my log file is huge so it's going to be a pain. I also agree with you that 2handers do more damage than most dual wield setups. SoD is pretty good damage for a 1hb though, those 288 procs really add up <br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Actually I find procing one handers to be of more use in holding aggro against rogues, monks, and casters that nuke or dot a ton instead of debuff aggro. Debuff aggro is early and it's a pretty likely case that you don't get a proc early on. One taunt though and you've piggybacked and you're good.<br>
<br>
People doing a heavy stream of damage during the fight... well dual wield or 2hander, we aren't going to outdamage them 99% of the time. Even if we taunt successfully they can still take aggro right back. So we need something to trick the mob... to make it more mad than our DPS would indicate (so enter +hate procs, debuffs, stuns, etc). <br>
<br>
I also often switch to 2hander midfight if I have sufficent aggro procs from dual wield. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dumeshuhlbelk>Dumesh UhlBelk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 446<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/03 11:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5353.topic&index=24>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://bellsouthpwp.net/w/i/wilsonua/DumStare.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon to pair with Red Blade</span><hr size=1> Indeed, my eyes failed me on the shaman tanking.<br>
